string-array.name: changelogLast
string-array.item: Hearings now wait a few hours after starting to disappear from list.
Finally fixed our district maps: replaced with Mapbox, displayed in-app
Clicking on the Call button now immediately begins a call
Nearly all web requests for Congressional information now use an encrypted connection (HTTPS)
Buttons to jump to legislators\' Twitter, YouTube, and Facebook accounts

string-array.name: changelog
string-array.item: 4.6.1 - Fixed a crash affecting some users when visiting legislator screens.
Unfortunately: we\'ve had to remove the News tab. Google announced their API shutdown years ago, and no viable alternative has emerged.
Fortunately: now displaying more context for votes on nominations, bills, and amendments. (For example, names of nominees.)
Show a party leadership title for members of Congress, if they have one.
Using new and improved source for photos of members of Congress.
If your device doesn\'t have GPS or network location, the location button will be hidden.
Updated our district maps to be scrollable, zoom-able, and more stable.
Various bug fixes and invisible improvements.
